Sure ‚Äî I‚Äôll break it down **clearly and properly, step by step** üëá

Your command:

```powershell
irm https://dub.sh/nahid | iex
```

This has **three main parts**:

---

# üîπ Part 1 ‚Äî `irm`

`irm` = **Invoke-RestMethod**

Full form:

```powershell
Invoke-RestMethod
```

üëâ What it does:

It **downloads (fetches) the content of a URL** and prints it as text in PowerShell.

So this part:

```powershell
irm https://dub.sh/nahid
```

means:

> ‚ÄúGo to this link and get whatever text/script is there.‚Äù

If you ran ONLY this:

```powershell
irm https://dub.sh/nahid
```

You would just see the script printed on your screen.

---

# üîπ Part 2 ‚Äî The Pipe `|`

The pipe (`|`) means:

> ‚ÄúTake the output from the left side and send it to the right side.‚Äù

So:

```powershell
irm https://dub.sh/nahid | iex
```

Means:

> Take whatever comes from the website and pass it to `iex`.

---

# üîπ Part 3 ‚Äî `iex`

`iex` = **Invoke-Expression**

Full form:

```powershell
Invoke-Expression
```

üëâ What it does:

It **executes whatever text it receives as PowerShell code**.

So when you do:

```powershell
irm https://dub.sh/nahid | iex
```

You are basically saying:

> ‚ÄúDownload a script from this URL and immediately run it.‚Äù

---

# ‚úÖ Put together ‚Äî Plain English meaning

This command means:

> Download the script from `https://dub.sh/nahid` and run it directly in PowerShell.

It is equivalent to:

1. Download script
2. Then manually run it

But both are done in **one line automatically**.

---

# ‚ö†Ô∏è Important Security Note (very important to understand)

This pattern:

```powershell
irm <url> | iex
```

is **very dangerous** if you don‚Äôt trust the URL.

Why?

Because:

* You are **blindly executing code from the internet**
* That code can:

  * Delete files
  * Steal data
  * Install malware
  * Take control of your system

üí° **Safer alternative (recommended when learning):**

First check what you are about to run:

```powershell
irm https://dub.sh/nahid
```

If the script looks safe, **then** run it manually.

